{"start":{"row":69,"column":34},"end":{"row":69,"column":35},"action":"insert","lines":["t"],"id":34}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":30},"end":{"row":69,"column":35},"action":"remove","lines":["event"],"id":35},{"start":{"row":69,"column":30},"end":{"row":69,"column":31},"action":"insert","lines":["g"]}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":31},"end":{"row":69,"column":32},"action":"insert","lines":["a"],"id":36}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":32},"end":{"row":69,"column":33},"action":"insert","lines":["l"],"id":37}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":33},"end":{"row":69,"column":34},"action":"insert","lines":["l"],"id":38}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":34},"end":{"row":69,"column":35},"action":"insert","lines":["e"],"id":39}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":35},"end":{"row":69,"column":36},"action":"insert","lines":["r"],"id":40}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":36},"end":{"row":69,"column":37},"action":"insert","lines":["y"],"id":41}],[{"start":{"row":55,"column":33},"end":{"row":55,"column":510},"action":"remove","lines":["With a goal to empower people technologically in designing a greater tomorrow, Miracle has conducted AIOUG (All India Oracle Users Group) Vizag Chapter, a technical event that yielded a part of its initiatives for this year. And, it brought ahead a humble responsibility to energize society through technology put forward a step towards a better digital world. The event started on a successful note with an array of achievements and consistent exploration of new technologies."],"id":42},{"start":{"row":55,"column":33},"end":{"row":56,"column":0},"action":"insert","lines":["An initiative from Miracle Software Systems, the dream of Our beloved CEO & President Prasad Lokam to create 1,00,000 digital professionals in AP was launched on August 5th, 2016 in the presence of Honourable Chief Guest Minister for IT and Communications, Dr. Palle Raghunatha Reddy, Honourable Ministers Sri Chintakayala Ayyanna Patrudu and Smt. Kimidi Mrunalini, IT Company Executives, AP Cloud Ambassadors and  Coaches, Media, and other delegates at Dr. Y V S Murthy Auditorium of AU College of Engineering, Visakhapatnam, The City of Destiny.",""]}],[{"start":{"row":59,"column":0},"end":{"row":62,"column":17},"action":"remove","lines":["<div class=\"row\">","             <img class=\"col-sm-12 img-responsive\" src=\"../images/events/aioug-group.png\"></img>","    ","           </div>"],"id":43}],[{"start":{"row":61,"column":32},"end":{"row":61,"column":462},"action":"remove","lines":["Miracle Heights being the venue, this wonderful event on <strong> June 18th, 2016 </strong> has attracted a crowd of 70 members who took an opportunity of exploring knowledge originating from giant organisations like IBM, Fluent Grid, Tech Mahindra, Terasoft, and APEPDCL (Eastern Power). And, in some of the slots were the toppers of Miracle Educational Society given a chance to learn about the latest and trending technologies."],"id":44},{"start":{"row":61,"column":32},"end":{"row":62,"column":0},"action":"insert","lines":["The event was initiated with a devotional prayer song along with that a poem was delivered with valuable words which added an elegance to the occasion of the AP cloud.  Lightning of the lamp was inaugurated by Smt. Mrunalini and Mrs. Madhavi Lokam accompanied in lighting up. And there was a divine presence over the auditorium with the Lamp Lightning. Smt. Mrunalini, Sri CH. Ayyanapatrudu, Sri Palle Raghunatha Reddy and Prasad Lokam delivered their valuable and inspirational speeches which energized every individual.",""]}],[{"start":{"row":64,"column":32},"end":{"row":64,"column":508},"action":"remove","lines":["<strong>Satyendra Oracle ACE Director - AIOUG </strong>through his remarkable sessions on Performance Tuning, Oracle 12c New Features, BigData, Hadoop, and Cloud for DBAs  had given a splendid time for all the attendees. He was excited with the crowd around and the ambiance at the venue for it was their very first event in Visakhapatnam, the City of Destiny. On behalf of AIOUG, he presented gifts to Database Team and the volunteers from HR, and Marketing teams of Miracle."],"id":45},{"start":{"row":64,"column":32},"end":{"row":65,"column":0},"action":"insert","lines":["An inspiration rich Presentation by our <b>Director of Marketing and Innovation, Chanakya Lokam</b> has given a glimpse of the AP Cloud’s vision followed by <b>Thanusha Deepthi from AP Cloud team</b> giving a brief view of AP Cloud’s mission and the trending technologies. To officially kick start the AP Cloud Initiative for the student and professionals, <b>AP Cloud Website, YouTube Channel,</b> and <b>Social Media Page</b> were launched by the the Chief Guest and the Guests of Honour at the Inaugural Ceremony.",""]}],[{"start":{"row":66,"column":32},"end":{"row":66,"column":626},"action":"remove","lines":["<strong>Vinay Malla </strong> from <strong>MIracle Software Systems, Inc.</strong> who took over the absolute responsibility of the event was lucky enough to inaugurate, and also deliver an outstanding session on Oracle 12c Architecture Enhancements and New Features. He was awarded a memento and was also handed over the responsibility of the upcoming AIOUG Vizag Chapter events. And, he announced that such technical events will be conducted regularly to deliver tremendous sessions in the future as well. It not only was a great event but also another triumph of Miracle’s Technical Journey."],"id":46},{"start":{"row":66,"column":32},"end":{"row":67,"column":0},"action":"insert","lines":["A 3-day workshop was conducted from August 5th-7th at Miracle Heights for educating the people on cloud technologies, a vision of our <b>Honorable Chief Minister, Sri Nara Chandrababu Naidu.</b> Our <b>CEO Prasad Lokam</b> delivered a presentation on Digital Transformation Services followed by sessions on technologies like HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript and also Node.js, a part of MEAN Stack technologies.",""]}],[{"start":{"row":68,"column":4},"end":{"row":69,"column":0},"action":"insert","lines":["",""],"id":47}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":0},"end":{"row":69,"column":23},"action":"insert","lines":[" <p class=\"methodText\">"],"id":48}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":23},"end":{"row":69,"column":24},"action":"insert","lines":["<"],"id":49}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":24},"end":{"row":69,"column":25},"action":"insert","lines":["/"],"id":50}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":25},"end":{"row":69,"column":26},"action":"insert","lines":["p"],"id":51}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":26},"end":{"row":69,"column":27},"action":"insert","lines":[">"],"id":52}],[{"start":{"row":69,"column":23},"end":{"row":71,"column":1},"action":"insert","lines":["","   "," "],"id":53}],[{"start":{"row":70,"column":3},"end":{"row":71,"column":0},"action":"insert","lines":["In addition to that, the workshop continued with the session on Express.js while also letting the participants perform in 2 hands-on labs, i.e the basic and the CRUD operations. Further more sessions were conducted on NoSQL MongoDB, and Express.js. With content rich sessions, innovative labs, and interesting discussion forums on different technologies, the workshop ignited great momentum and was concluded with a Question and Answers session in which gifts were distributed to the winners.",""],"id":54}],[{"start":{"row":55,"column":103},"end":{"row":55,"column":104},"action":"insert","lines":["<"],"id":55}],[{"start":{"row":55,"column":104},"end":{"row":55,"column":105},"action":"insert","lines":["s"],"id":56}],[{"start":{"row":55,"column":105},"end":{"row":55,"column":106},"action":"insert","lines":["t"],"id":57},{"start":{"row":55,"column":106},"end":{"row":55,"column":107},"action":"insert","lines":["r"]}],[{"start":{"row":55,"column":107},"end":{"row":55,"column":108},"action":"insert","lines":["o"],"id":58}],[{"start":{"row":55,"column":108},"end":{"row":55,"column":109},"action":"insert","lines":["n"],"id":59}],[{"start":{"row":55,"column":109},"end":{"row":55,"column":110},"action":"inse